+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XY5x3cSXwaqoEcQQYBoCYk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Consensus is unavailable (no API keys configured). I'll proceed with standard autopilot mode, making design decisions autonomously.\n\n**Autopilot Mode - Design Decisions:**\n\n**Q1: How should we generate unique IDs?**\n→ Choosing: **uuid library** - Already in dependencies, provides truly unique IDs, no collision risk.\n\n**Q2: What data structures for in-memory storage?**\n→ Choosing: **Map<string, T>** - TypeScript Maps provide O(1) lookup by ID, type-safe, and idiomatic.\n\n**Q3: How should services handle EventBus emit (sync vs async)?**\n→ Choosing: **Fire-and-forget from synchronous methods** - The bus.emit() is async, but most service methods are synchronous per the interfaces. We'll emit without awaiting where the interface doesn't return a Promise. Only Payment.processPayment returns a Promise.\n\n**Q4: How should Payment simulate success/failure/timeout?**\n→ Choosing: **Options object with mode field** - Pass `{ simulateFailure?: boolean, simulateTimeout?: boolean, timeoutMs?: number }` to the factory. Default is success.\n\n**Q5: How should Analytics track metrics?**\n→ Choosing: **Subscribe to all relevant events in the factory, maintain counters in Maps** - Simple aggregation pattern, track event counts, revenue, unique carts, orders, and product quantities.\n\n**Q6: How should Notifications track order-to-user mappings?**\n→ Choosing: **Listen for ORDER_CREATED events** to build orderId→userId mapping, then use it when ORDER_STATUS_CHANGED and PAYMENT_PROCESSED events arrive.\n\n**Q7: How should Pricing track product prices?**\n→ Choosing: **Listen for PRODUCT_CREATED events** and store productId→price in a Map. Also allow getPrice to be called directly.\n\nLet me now write the design document and then implement."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_